#skincaretip #utilizeyourproducts 
Winter season usually makes face and hair washes a little thicker than usual. 
It is therefore important that you take the time to emulsify your product properly with water before using it. 
Not emulsifying face washes will make you rub the product on your face more vigorously in order to form the lather potentially damaging your barrier. It might also not cleanse your face properly and lead to acne. 
Not emulsifying hair washes will make the product sit on your scalp in a thicker consistency which is difficult to be washed off with water. It also might leave your scalp not cleansed properly and causing you to use more product. That can potentially make your hair frizzy and also empty the product faster. 

So my frens, emulsify the fuck out of your washes. 

#emulsify #facewashing #hairwashing #wintertips #winterskincare #winterhaircare #skincarecontent #haircaretip

#skincarebasics MOISTURIZING

Irrespective of your skin type, in my opinion, moisturizing twice is the real deal. I have had oily skin and now I have dry skin and both the times have made me acknowledge how important it is to moisturize my face. 
Moisturizer is primarily essential to lock in the hydration that your skin already has and/or the hydration provided to your skin through products. It traps the hydration to make your skin look healthy and glowy. 
If you skip the moisturizer, your skin becomes more susceptible to tewl (trans epidermal water loss) which can cause dry and dehydrated skin. 
A lot of moisturizers now have active ingredients to help you with skin issues too and even when they don’t seep in as deep as serums possibly can, they are still a go to when you’re not willing to invest in serums. 

Don’t shy away from using moisturizers for there’s a variety of textures available to suit every skin type. 
For #dryskin go with thicker creams with ceramides and calming ingredients since this season can take a toll on your skin. 
For #normalskin to #combinationskin lotions are your bffs. They’re not too heavy and neither absorb too quickly to make your face feel stretchy. 
For #oilyskin light gel based moisturizers can be your go to. 

These are just references honestly since I have used lotions on my oily skin and gels on my dry skin. It basically depends on the formulation and how the product works for you. 

The point is, DON’T SKIP THE MOISTURIZER! 

#winterskincare #moisturizer #skincare #contentcreator #facelotion #facegel #facecream

latestPosts.caption:
Hi ✨
So this is about me since I haven’t done this here yet. 
My name’s Somya (Som for you all) and I got into skincare because I have had acne almost all my life. I had been bullied, borderline depressed, and insecure for a very very long time because of acne; I had self esteem issues back when I was a teenager because of how I looked. 
I have till now been on 3 rounds of isotretnoin (each lasted almost 1-2 months only since my acne was 70% healed by then) and my last dose was back in Jan 2019. 
It was in Feb 2020 that I first ordered @deciem @theordinary from @cultbeauty that sparked my interest in skincare. I had ordered Niacinamide 10% + Zinc 1% and somehow, I just kept on digging and finding about ingredients and how they function post that. 
I started this page in June 2020 after being pushed by my sister, @masala_omlette since I always used to tell her how I’d spend all my savings on skincare. Back then, I was hoarding products since I was always triggered by the slightest spot and didn’t want to go back on isotretnoin. Fast forward to today, I’m trying to be a much more confident person in terms of handling my skin and my skincare ingredients. 
I’ve come a long way to take the journey of self love through skincare and I hope that I can give a percent of that positivity and awareness to you ♥️ 
That’s why I say, #happyskincare 

📸 @untamedkalakaar
